[2] Thailand, disease recurrence
Date: Mon 15 Jan 2007
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Reuters Alertnet [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/BKK229732.htm>

Thailand has 1st bird flu outbreak in 6 months
----------------------------------------------
Thailand has suffered its 1st outbreak of the H5N1 bird flu virus in 6
months, an Agriculture Ministry official said on Monday [15 Jan 2007],
after a rash of outbreaks in Viet Nam and 4 human deaths in Indonesia this
year. "The lab results confirmed that some ducks in the northern province
of Phitsanulok have been infected with H5N1 bird flu virus," Livestock
Department chief Pirom Srichan told Reuters. "We have culled about 1900
ducks in the area."
The last outbreak of the virus in poultry in Thailand was in late July 2006.
